edmund charles blunden, cbe, mc (1 november 1896 â€“ 20 january 1974) was an english poet, author and critic. like his friend siegfried sassoon, he wrote of his experiences in world war i in both verse and prose. for most of his career, blunden was also a reviewer for english publications and an academic in tokyo and later hong kong. he ended his career as professor of poetry at the university of oxford.